    Description
    Athlete
    The Athlete class stores relevant information about athletes who finish the races, enabling quick results summarization with names, grades, previous PRs, and other relevant imformation

    CameraStarter
    CameraStarter uses the microphone to immediately start races when the amplitude of sound exceeds a certain theshold.
    CompositeFrame
    CompositeFrame represents the final image with timestamped image slivers.
    DraggableLine
    DraggableLine class stores information about each of the draggable lines created in PostTimingGUI.
    ImageProcessing
     
    LiveTimingGUI
    LiveTimingGUI is the Main component of FinishCam.
    OCRCapture
    Handles capturing a stream from a second camera used for OCR hip number recognition
    OutputProcessor
    OutputProcessor handles the summarization of results in various formats
    PostTimingGUI
    The PostTImingGUI class is called by LiveTiminGUI and adds draggable lines corresponding to each athlete.
    SingleFrame
    SingleFrame holds a frame of the camera capture with a timestamp
    ThreadedCameraRunner
    ThreadedCameraRunner handles the real-time control and capturing of camera data used for creating the finish image and optionally runs OCR by offloading to OCRCapture.
    TimeFormat
    Holds Time data in a way that is intuitively displayed and compatible with system times.
